note.body:
See !135 for the rest of the find dialog go "BOOM" fix.  This (!134) was a reactive fix, since the ops variable was NULL, or random.

What was happening is that the first time find dialog was launched it was initialized with the current diagram.  Then instead of destroying and reinitializing the find dialog, it was hidden and then reshown when next launched.

I have been editing the dia diagram by hand, then closing and showing the diagram to catch the effects of the edits.

Without the change for !135, the hidden find dialog would have an internal pointer to the destroyed diagram and not a pointer to the current diagram.  Thus the garbage pointers of the find dialog's user_data and SearchData structure would SEGFAULT wherever used.

I still like the progressive checks, proposed here, i.e. the middle check was missing:
```
  g_return_if_fail (self != NULL);
  g_return_if_fail (self->ops != NULL);
  g_return_if_fail (self->ops->`some ops member` != NULL);
```

```suggestion:-1+0
          xs = fabs ((double) x2 / width);
          ys = fabs ((double) y2 / height);
```

We have a space before the `(` in function calls (at least on new/updated code), also `double` instead of `real`
